        "creation_date": 1585898968,
        "body": "<p>I have used <strong>JUnit 5's Temporary Directory(<code>@TempDir<\/code>)<\/strong> functionality to create a temporary directory and then pass the directory path to <code>Files.write()<\/code> method (along with the file name of course). The <code>@TempDir<\/code> will delete the files and temporary folder, it created, once the test execution is done. This way, I was able to execute the test case.<\/p>\n",
